[30;1m116 | [0m[35m        service checks the hash of the content that has arrived with the hash[0m
[30;1m117 | [0m[35m        that was sent. This is primarily valuable for detecting bitflips on[0m
[30;1m118 | [0m[35m        the wire if using http instead of https as https (the default) will[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35m        already validate. Note that this MD5 hash is not stored with the[0m
